00:12:24.480 --> 00:12:26.440
as a Jewish person, there was a set route

00:12:26.440 --> 00:12:27.280
that you would take.

00:12:27.280 --> 00:12:29.040
There was a way that you would go

00:12:29.040 --> 00:12:32.540
and you would never go through Samaria.

00:12:32.540 --> 00:12:34.160
It just was the way it was.

00:12:34.160 --> 00:12:35.160
And why?

00:12:35.160 --> 00:12:40.080
Well, the woman at the well says this to him,

00:12:40.080 --> 00:12:42.680
why is it that you ask me of water?

00:12:42.680 --> 00:12:46.540
The Jews have no company with the Samaritans.

00:12:46.540 --> 00:12:49.300
There's this divide, this prejudice,

00:12:49.300 --> 00:12:52.520
and we look at that and we understand that it says

00:12:52.520 --> 00:12:55.320
in verse nine, for the Jews have no dealing

00:12:55.320 --> 00:12:56.300
with the Samaritans.

00:12:56.300 --> 00:12:59.140
They would literally go out of their way.

00:12:59.140 --> 00:13:03.880
They would take a longer journey in order to avoid Samaria.

00:13:04.880 --> 00:13:05.880
How many of you ever take a trip

00:13:05.880 --> 00:13:08.360
and you take the shortcut, right?

00:13:08.360 --> 00:13:10.600
And sometimes you try to outsmart your GPS.

00:13:10.600 --> 00:13:12.360
You ever try to do that and you find out

00:13:12.360 --> 00:13:14.840
that the GPS actually was smarter than you were

00:13:14.840 --> 00:13:17.960
and was taking you on the route that it was on purpose.

00:13:17.960 --> 00:13:20.000
I remember talking to a little kid years ago

00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:22.300
and I asked how a trip was and they said it was really good.

00:13:23.080 --> 00:13:25.540
We took the long cut and I thought that was quite comical

00:13:25.540 --> 00:13:27.620
to hear the child use that terminology.

00:13:27.620 --> 00:13:29.100
What do you mean by taking the long cut?

00:13:29.100 --> 00:13:31.940
Well, my dad missed the turn and we took the long way.

00:13:31.940 --> 00:13:34.080
And I mean, it just right out there, you know,

00:13:34.080 --> 00:13:36.820
and it was quite comical, but really the Jews,

00:13:36.820 --> 00:13:37.660
that's what they would do.

00:13:37.660 --> 00:13:41.360
They would go out of their way to avoid Samaria.

00:13:41.360 --> 00:13:43.100
But notice in verse number four, the Bible says,

00:13:43.100 --> 00:13:48.100
and he must, needs go through Samaria.

00:13:50.300 --> 00:13:51.580
Why?

00:13:51.580 --> 00:13:53.540
Well, because he walked purposefully.

00:13:54.360 --> 00:13:56.140
He walked purposefully.

00:13:56.140 --> 00:13:59.380
We find that he comes and you're familiar with the account.

00:13:59.380 --> 00:14:00.900
Then cometh he to a city of Samaria,

00:14:00.900 --> 00:14:03.620
which is called Sychar, near to the parcel of ground

00:14:03.620 --> 00:14:06.000
that Jacob gave to his son Joseph.

00:14:06.000 --> 00:14:07.860
Verse six, now Jacob's well was there.

00:14:07.860 --> 00:14:10.180
Jesus therefore being wearied with his journey,

00:14:10.180 --> 00:14:13.180
sat thus on the well and it was about the sixth hour.

00:14:13.180 --> 00:14:15.780
Then cometh a woman of Samaria to draw water

00:14:15.780 --> 00:14:19.000
and Jesus saith unto her, give me to drink.

00:14:19.000 --> 00:14:20.420
Now we don't have time this evening

00:14:20.420 --> 00:14:22.340
to look at the entirety of the fourth chapter

00:14:22.340 --> 00:14:25.620
of the book of John, but I believe tonight I could say,

00:14:25.620 --> 00:14:27.160
and most of us are familiar with it,

00:14:27.160 --> 00:14:28.600
that you would agree with me,

00:14:28.600 --> 00:14:32.660
that her life was never the same after this interaction.

00:14:32.660 --> 00:14:37.660
And what a joy to think about how Jesus walked purposefully.

00:14:37.660 --> 00:14:40.779
That though so many, if they're going to go

00:14:40.779 --> 00:14:44.580
from Judea to Galilee, they would go a certain route.

00:14:44.580 --> 00:14:47.980
They would avoid at all costs going through Samaria.

00:14:47.980 --> 00:14:52.100
No, Jesus said that he must needs go through Samaria.

00:14:53.100 --> 00:14:54.860
He walked with purpose.

00:14:54.860 --> 00:14:59.860
I think about the woman at the well and her being saved,

00:14:59.900 --> 00:15:04.100
but also the people of the city that heard and came,

00:15:04.100 --> 00:15:05.860
and not only from her testimony,

00:15:05.860 --> 00:15:09.620
but from hearing as Jesus stayed there for two days

00:15:09.620 --> 00:15:10.820
and teaching and preaching

00:15:10.820 --> 00:15:13.720
and how many came to know the Lord.

00:15:13.720 --> 00:15:15.620
Man, isn't that awesome?

00:15:15.620 --> 00:15:17.779
He walked purposefully.

00:15:18.580 --> 00:15:19.620
And so if we understand this evening,

00:15:19.620 --> 00:15:22.840
the truth of 1 John 2 in verse number six,

00:15:22.840 --> 00:15:26.700
where the Bible says, again, just as a reminder,

00:15:26.700 --> 00:15:28.940
he that saith he abideth in him

00:15:28.940 --> 00:15:33.140
ought himself also so to walk even as he walked.

00:15:33.140 --> 00:15:35.320
And so if we can look at the scriptures,

00:15:35.320 --> 00:15:37.140
and again, there's a number of other portions

00:15:37.140 --> 00:15:38.700
of scripture that we could go to,

00:15:38.700 --> 00:15:43.140
and we could prove tonight that Jesus walked purposefully,

00:15:43.140 --> 00:15:45.580
then it should be said of us as the people of God

00:15:45.580 --> 00:15:48.500
that we too should walk purposefully.

00:15:48.500 --> 00:15:50.220
We should have purpose.

00:15:50.220 --> 00:15:51.380
I wonder this evening,

00:15:51.380 --> 00:15:52.980
sometimes people ask this question,

00:15:52.980 --> 00:15:55.020
what is the purpose of life?

00:15:55.020 --> 00:15:57.100
What is, why are we here?

00:15:57.100 --> 00:15:58.340
You know, it's kind of interesting

00:15:58.340 --> 00:16:00.059
when you hear people ask that question,

00:16:00.059 --> 00:16:01.820
and depending on their worldview,

00:16:01.820 --> 00:16:04.059
you get a varied kind of answer.

00:16:04.059 --> 00:16:06.860
And people have all sorts of ideas and thoughts

00:16:06.860 --> 00:16:10.160
with regard to why they're here and what their purpose is.

00:16:10.160 --> 00:16:11.279
But I would submit to you

00:16:11.279 --> 00:16:13.740
that as a child of God this evening,

00:16:13.740 --> 00:16:17.900
that we should not have any stuttering or stammering,

00:16:17.900 --> 00:16:20.300
it should not be any difficulty for us

00:16:20.300 --> 00:16:23.540
to be able to answer with confidence and clarity

00:16:23.540 --> 00:16:25.080
what our purpose is.

00:16:25.940 --> 00:16:28.680
Because our purpose can be summarized very easily

00:16:28.680 --> 00:16:31.300
as we read the truth of 1 Corinthians 10,

00:16:31.300 --> 00:16:33.260
and verse number 31, where the Bible says,

00:16:33.260 --> 00:16:35.779
whether therefore you eat, or drink,

00:16:35.779 --> 00:16:38.200
or whatsoever you do,

00:16:38.200 --> 00:16:43.200
do all to the glory of God.

00:16:43.640 --> 00:16:45.120
Is that what your Bible says?

00:16:45.120 --> 00:16:46.360
That's what my Bible says.

00:16:46.360 --> 00:16:49.740
And so if we could take that verse of scripture tonight

00:16:49.740 --> 00:16:52.520
and use that verse as answering the question,

00:16:52.520 --> 00:16:53.740
what is my purpose?

00:16:53.740 --> 00:16:55.680
What's the purpose of my life?

00:16:55.680 --> 00:16:57.400
What is it that I'm doing?

00:16:57.400 --> 00:16:59.559
And no doubt there are times, I mean,

00:16:59.559 --> 00:17:02.200
businessmen, those in corporate America,

00:17:02.200 --> 00:17:05.120
they've struggled because they've kind of,

00:17:05.120 --> 00:17:06.940
if you kind of use that terminology

00:17:06.940 --> 00:17:08.380
of being in the rat races,

00:17:08.380 --> 00:17:11.200
they would use that analogy of just

00:17:11.200 --> 00:17:13.600
how high up the ladder can I climb?

00:17:13.600 --> 00:17:15.040
How much can I make?

00:17:15.040 --> 00:17:16.920
What titles can I attain?

00:17:16.920 --> 00:17:18.700
And reality sets in.

00:17:18.700 --> 00:17:21.380
There's always somewhere else to go.

00:17:21.380 --> 00:17:24.040
There's always someone else competing.

00:17:24.040 --> 00:17:25.980
And what is our purpose?

00:17:26.960 --> 00:17:28.760
I had a professor in Bible college

00:17:28.760 --> 00:17:31.279
that I remember with great clarity,

00:17:31.279 --> 00:17:32.880
him coming into class one day

00:17:32.880 --> 00:17:35.820
with just a different countenance.

00:17:35.820 --> 00:17:38.920
You ever notice somebody that has a different countenance

00:17:38.920 --> 00:17:40.680
and you try to figure out,

00:17:41.160 --> 00:17:42.000
okay, what's going on?

00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:43.880
Remember, Nehemiah had a countenance.

00:17:43.880 --> 00:17:45.040
His countenance was sad.

00:17:45.040 --> 00:17:48.800
It was sorrow of heart is what the king said.

00:17:48.800 --> 00:17:50.600
And we find that you can tell,

00:17:50.600 --> 00:17:52.160
you can read people, you sometimes,

00:17:52.160 --> 00:17:53.440
especially if you know them,

00:17:53.440 --> 00:17:54.279
you can just see them and say,

00:17:54.279 --> 00:17:55.100
hey, what's wrong?

00:17:55.100 --> 00:17:57.240
Like, I can just tell there's something not right.

00:17:57.240 --> 00:17:59.760
And I remember the professor walking in

00:17:59.760 --> 00:18:03.559
and this just sobriety that was over him

00:18:03.559 --> 00:18:06.680
and we began to inquire and we found out

00:18:06.680 --> 00:18:08.400
that there were just some things

00:18:08.400 --> 00:18:09.980
that he had been talking about

00:18:10.059 --> 00:18:11.220
with regard to purpose.

00:18:11.220 --> 00:18:15.180
And he was just overwhelmed with the fact

00:18:15.180 --> 00:18:18.860
that God saved him and God called him to the ministry.

00:18:18.860 --> 00:18:23.820
And he was just so full of emotion over that.

00:18:23.820 --> 00:18:24.660
And here's why.

00:18:24.660 --> 00:18:26.820
He began to tell us the account of his life

00:18:26.820 --> 00:18:31.420
and how he grew up in a home where they weren't saved.

00:18:31.420 --> 00:18:33.220
They didn't go to church,

00:18:33.220 --> 00:18:35.419
except for a couple of times a year,

00:18:35.419 --> 00:18:38.179
kind of the special holidays and that sort of thing,

00:18:38.179 --> 00:18:42.320
and went to college and trained for a particular field.

00:18:42.320 --> 00:18:43.859
He was in the engineering field

00:18:43.859 --> 00:18:45.660
and that's what he was gonna do.

00:18:45.660 --> 00:18:48.220
And he said that he was a design engineer

00:18:48.220 --> 00:18:50.859
working on things and machinery and so on and so forth.

00:18:50.859 --> 00:18:52.480
And he got this job and man,

00:18:52.480 --> 00:18:54.020
he thought he was at the top of the world

00:18:54.020 --> 00:18:55.619
and all these things out of college

00:18:55.619 --> 00:18:58.460
and successful several years at the same company.

00:18:58.460 --> 00:19:00.260
And they had this big ceremony

00:19:00.260 --> 00:19:04.059
where they had worked on designing this new machine

00:19:04.059 --> 00:19:06.780
and they were taking out all of the old stuff

00:19:06.780 --> 00:19:07.820
and putting in the new

00:19:08.460 --> 00:19:10.020
and they had this big ribbon cutting ceremony

00:19:10.020 --> 00:19:11.020
and all these things.

00:19:11.020 --> 00:19:14.140
And as all of this is happening,

00:19:14.140 --> 00:19:16.980
just a few weeks prior, he got saved.

00:19:18.140 --> 00:19:19.179
Somebody invited him to church

00:19:19.179 --> 00:19:21.500
and he went to church and he got saved.

00:19:21.500 --> 00:19:26.100
And all he had been living for was that type of an event.

00:19:26.100 --> 00:19:28.460
But something changed in his heart and his life.

00:19:28.460 --> 00:19:31.580
And he knew that that wasn't what life was all about.

00:19:31.580 --> 00:19:32.960
And God was working in his heart,

00:19:32.960 --> 00:19:34.940
calling to the ministry and so on and so forth.

00:19:35.059 --> 00:19:37.859
And he said, I stood at that ribbon cutting ceremony

00:19:37.859 --> 00:19:42.380
and here's the thought that just was so impressed on my heart

00:19:42.380 --> 00:19:46.980
is that one day, another group of people are gonna come in

00:19:46.980 --> 00:19:50.380
and they're gonna take out the machines that I helped design

00:19:50.380 --> 00:19:52.859
and they're gonna implement new machines

00:19:52.859 --> 00:19:54.900
and they're gonna have a ribbon cutting ceremony

00:19:54.900 --> 00:19:59.739
and it's gonna happen over and over and over again.

00:19:59.739 --> 00:20:05.179
And God used that in his life to help him understand and solidify the call.

00:20:05.179 --> 00:20:07.819
Now, we understand not everyone's called to the ministry.

00:20:09.019 --> 00:20:10.779
But for him, he'd been struggling with that.

00:20:10.779 --> 00:20:14.059
I mean, right after he got saved, God was dealing with him calling to the ministry,

00:20:14.059 --> 00:20:15.899
and he was really struggling with that.

00:20:15.899 --> 00:20:18.539
And he said, look, what is life all about?

00:20:18.539 --> 00:20:20.139
Is this what I want to do?

00:20:20.139 --> 00:20:23.099
And the reality is that God was calling him.

00:20:23.099 --> 00:20:25.899
Again, God's not calling everyone to the ministry.

00:20:25.899 --> 00:20:32.219
But what we must understand is that wherever we are, if we're an engineer, if we're a doctor,

00:20:32.219 --> 00:20:40.539
if we're in economics, finance, medicine, whatever field we're in, that God has for us,

00:20:41.179 --> 00:20:44.139
that whatsoever we do, we do it for his glory.

00:20:45.179 --> 00:20:52.219
Whatsoever thy hand findeth to do, do it heartily as unto the Lord and not unto men.

00:20:52.219 --> 00:20:57.739
And so we find that at some point in life, as we recognize, what is my purpose?

00:20:57.739 --> 00:21:01.979
And how do I walk purposefully as Jesus did?

00:21:01.979 --> 00:21:07.179
How do I fulfill the purpose of whether therefore you eat, drink, or whatsoever you do,

00:21:07.179 --> 00:21:08.699
do all to the glory of God?

00:21:08.699 --> 00:21:10.139
I think about that verse of Scripture.

00:21:10.139 --> 00:21:14.939
In fact, several weeks ago, in our marriage class, I used that verse of Scripture

00:21:15.499 --> 00:21:17.659
as one of the points in our lesson.

00:21:17.659 --> 00:21:21.259
And I said this, it's always an interesting verse of Scripture, because for me,

00:21:21.259 --> 00:21:25.019
the thought of eating or drinking is just a, you almost don't think about it.

00:21:25.019 --> 00:21:28.139
I mean, it's just a natural, you have to, right?

00:21:28.139 --> 00:21:31.019
I mean, your body reminds you if you don't.

00:21:31.019 --> 00:21:36.059
And it's just kind of almost a mundane kind of a thing.

00:21:37.739 --> 00:21:44.139
But God says, whether you eat or drink or whatsoever you do, do all to the glory of God.

00:21:44.139 --> 00:21:45.819
And so how do I do it to the glory of God?

00:21:45.819 --> 00:21:49.419
How do I walk with that purpose, understanding the purpose?

00:21:49.899 --> 00:21:53.499
Mark 16, 15, a verse that we are very familiar with,

00:21:53.499 --> 00:22:00.699
a verse that some of the liberal Bible folks today try to take out of the Bible,

00:22:01.339 --> 00:22:06.619
textual critics, and they try to discount the closing portion of Mark 16.

00:22:07.419 --> 00:22:12.859
Many of them will explain away the Great Commission from the other books as well.

00:22:12.859 --> 00:22:19.339
But we find Mark 16, 15, that Jesus makes it very plain to the disciples,

00:22:19.339 --> 00:22:20.379
and he said unto them,

00:22:20.379 --> 00:22:25.339
go ye into all the world and preach the gospel to every creature.

00:22:25.339 --> 00:22:29.419
And the reality is that we have a unique privilege and opportunity.

00:22:29.419 --> 00:22:32.139
We've been allowed of God to preach the gospel.

00:22:32.139 --> 00:22:36.539
Now, does it mean that everything I'm going to do every single day of my life,

00:22:36.539 --> 00:22:38.779
all I'm going to do is go and preach the gospel?

